<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/126.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Cabinet has decided, subject to the approval of Chang Chien,<note n="41" xml:id="d110fn41">Minister of Agriculture and
                                Commerce.</note> that the Government will guarantee payment of the
                            cost of supplementary <pb facs="0224" n="108" xml:id="pg_108"/> survey
                            up to $100,000 gold if the necessary funds are advanced by the Red Cross
                            and the White Company. As soon as Chang Chien has been heard from,
                            instructions will be issued to Shah.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>